reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Upgraded my sons computer
reviews.reviewText: I won't even pretend to have the lingo to review this with any degree of technical specs. I don't and I can't.BUT, as a MOM who has had three sons over the course of three decades, play video games, I can say - I don't hear as much yelling.I'm not a gamer, but I have come to learn that words like "lagging" and "buffering" and "effed up" mean something is bad. And my son was saying (or yelling) that quite a bit.He got this and now his gaming has been going great. It's been a few months and no problems have popped up.He installed it himself without much issue. His games and apps run better and he said his streaming is better.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars The Asus ROG Strix Z790-F Gaming WiFi 2 is a solid mid-tier motherboard for Intel Raptor Lake-R...
reviews.reviewText: Pros:+Nice aesthetics, this a good looking motherboard, not over-the-top gamer styling+16 90-amp power stages+PCIe Gen 4 x4 lanes to the primary M.2 slot from the CPU (no bifurcation of the PCIe Gen 5 x16 GPU slot)+Easy to work with and build upon+I was able to get DDR5-8000 working (post + boot + benchmarks), much to my surprise, but more stability testing is needed before I can claim this is truly stable, YMMV+BIOS has far more levers to tinker with than my previous builds+Q-slot makes GPU removal/swapping so much easier+Typical excellent ASUS build qualityCons:+I believe it's only a 6-layer PCB, which is disappointing at this price tier+XMP profiles for DDR5-8000 don't work at all, I had to manually tune voltages and timings+BIOS options can be overwhelming with little explanationI'm currently focused on memory overclocking first and foremost. It's possible that DDR5-8000 won't be stable long-term, in which case I will have to back it down to somewhere between 7200-7800 MTS, as it is very unusual to get 8000 MTS stable on 4-dimm boards. After that, I intend to start overclocking the CPU.My current 14900K is very average, at least based upon the SP core ratings, but it may have a better than average memory controller, since the IMC is running at 2 GHz. I will try to update my review once I complete all of my testing.I got this board as kind of an experiment to see what can be done on a mid-range Z790 motherboard when it comes to CPU and memory overclocking, since this is the last hurrah for LGA1700.System Specs:Asus Z790-F Gaming Wifi 2Intel i9-14900K SP = 97 (P-core SP = 106, E-core SP = 80), PL1 = 195w, PL2 = 165w, Asus MCE disabledG.Skill Trident Z5 2x24 GB DDR5-8000 (40-48-48-48-128-2T @1.35v, gear 2), SK Hynix M-dieCorsair HX1500i2 GB Samsung 990 ProAsus ROG Strix LCII 360mm AIOOpen air test bench

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 21, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Very nice motherboard….paired with Dominator Titanium 7200 ram, no problem with xmp at 7200…tons of usb ports, plenty of power for anything you want to do..as with other Asus boards Wi-Fi does not work straight out the box..had to use external adapter to get it running then updated the driver and now it’s fine…I love that it has 5 m.2 slots..overall really solid board and looks awesome!
